desc:
The Akita DAO contract has several responsibilities:
[ ] Manages the disbursement of the bones token
[ ] Manages the disbursement of earned income
[x] Manages the content policy of the protocol
[x] Manages the minimum impact score to qualify for daily disbursement
[x] Manages service fees

version.desc: the version number of the DAO

contentPolicy.desc: the raw 36 byte content policy of the protocol

minRewardsImpact.desc: the minimum impact score to qualify for daily disbursement

akitaAppList.desc: the list of akita contract ids

pluginAppList.desc: the list of plugin contract ids

otherAppList.desc: the list of other contract ids we use

krbyPercentage.desc:
The percentage of total rewards allocated to krby expressed in the hundreds
eg. 3% is 300, 12.75% is 1275

proposalCreationSettings.desc: The default settings for creating proposals by proposal action

proposalParticipationSettings.desc: The default minimum participation needed for a proposal to be valid

proposalApprovalThresholdSettings.desc: The default threshold of approval votes needed for a proposal to pass

proposalVotingDurationSettings.desc: The default duration for which a proposal must be open for voting

lastChange.desc: The last time state has changed on the abstracted account (not including lastCalled for cooldowns) in unix time

spendingAddress.desc: [TEMPORARY STATE FIELD] The spending address for the currently active plugin

escrowFactory.desc: the spending account factory to use for allowances

plugins.desc: Plugins that add functionality to the controlledAddress and the account that has permission to use it.

namedPlugins.desc: Plugins that have been given a name for discoverability

escrows.desc: the escrows that this wallet has created for specific callers with allowances

receiveEscrows.desc: escrow accounts for services to payback revenue to the DAO

receiveAssets.desc: box map of escrow assets that have already been processed during this allocation

payoutEscrows.desc: escrow accounts meant to payout recipients

allowances.desc: The Allowances for plugins installed on the smart contract with useAllowance set to true
